# Case Study HTML

## File to edit

Edit `{project}-case-study/{project}-case-study.html`. Ignore each folder’s redirect-only `index.html`.

## Layout patterns

- Mobile breakpoint: `@media (max-width:900px)`.
- Tab panels: `.tab-panel` / `.tab-btn`; inactive panel media is deferred by `relay.js` — use folder tab structure, don’t eager-load hidden-tab videos.
- Mobile carousels: horizontal scroll + snap + dots (see Sifted `wire-carousel`, RapiMD `problem-carousel`, Diapulse `flow-carousel`).
- Accent colors: teal for headings/labels; coral for interactive tabs/accordions/CTAs (per-file audit comments at top of `<style>`).

## Assets

- Paths from case study pages: `/assets/{project}/...` (absolute).
- RapiMD asset folder on disk: `rapidmd` (not `rapimd`).
- Prefer MP4/WebM over GIF for large prototypes. Use `preload="metadata"` on non-hero videos; hero videos in `.hero-image` may use `preload="auto"`.
- Below-fold `img[data-relay]`: rely on `relay.js` lazy behavior; avoid inline `margin-top` on images.

## Links

- Back to work: `../#work`. Home: `../`.
- Next project: `../other-case-study/` (folder URL, not `.html` filename).
- Do not break the redirect chain: internal links → folder URL → folder `index.html` → labeled `.html` file.
